00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:55.670
The peripheral
nerves is the part

00:03:55.670 --> 00:03:57.890
of the nervous
system that's outside

00:03:57.890 --> 00:03:59.330
of the brain and
the spinal cord.

00:03:59.330 --> 00:04:01.163
That's what a lot of
people think about when

00:04:01.163 --> 00:04:02.690
they think of neurology.

00:04:02.690 --> 00:04:04.430
What we're talking
about today is

00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:09.260
the wiring that connects our
CPU to the outside world.

00:04:09.260 --> 00:04:13.370
When we take a cross-section
through a peripheral nerve

00:04:13.370 --> 00:04:16.970
of a human, we can see
these small fibers,

00:04:16.970 --> 00:04:19.100
which are the kind
of nerve axons

00:04:19.100 --> 00:04:21.470
that I'll be
talking about today.

00:04:21.470 --> 00:04:23.630
These are these tiny
little thin guys.

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:25.940
That's why they're
called small fibers.

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:28.880
There's a bunch of different
ones including C-fibers,

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:31.790
A-deltas, and autonomics.

00:04:31.790 --> 00:04:37.100
Because of these many different
functions, as you'll see,

00:04:37.100 --> 00:04:40.340
polyneuropathy can have
different medical causes,

00:04:40.340 --> 00:04:44.360
and cause different symptoms.

00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:47.850
The functions of
these small fibers

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:51.630
are so diverse that when
people develop neuropathies

00:04:51.630 --> 00:04:54.090
that affect them,
they can just develop

00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:56.070
a lot of different symptoms.

00:04:56.070 --> 00:04:59.010
And we're going to go over
some of those symptoms,

00:04:59.010 --> 00:05:01.290
but I think there's an
underlying problem, which

00:05:01.290 --> 00:05:04.860
is that a lot of patients who
have this kind of neuropathy,

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:06.720
it's not even picked up.

00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:08.440
They're searching for answers.

00:05:08.440 --> 00:05:11.580
They know they've got problems
in more than one organ system.

00:05:11.580 --> 00:05:14.590
People haven't put
the pieces together.

00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:18.510
It's like the blind
men and the elephant.

00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:21.180
So let's go over
some of the symptoms,

00:05:21.180 --> 00:05:24.190
and again, not every
patient has every symptoms,

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:26.470
and I'm not able to talk
about all of the symptoms.

00:05:26.470 --> 00:05:29.400
So I'm just focusing on
the most common ones,

00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:33.540
and clearly, one of them
is chronic widespread pain.

00:05:33.540 --> 00:05:36.750
That means it's not like
you fell down, and banged

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:38.760
your knee, and you
have pain in your leg,

00:05:38.760 --> 00:05:40.830
but it's really pain
affecting both sides

00:05:40.830 --> 00:05:43.890
of your body for
no clear reason,

00:05:43.890 --> 00:05:45.490
or no better explanation.

00:05:48.300 --> 00:05:51.780
Pain from small fiber neuropathy
comes in two varieties.

00:05:51.780 --> 00:05:56.130
So the most common is
so-called distal pain,

00:05:56.130 --> 00:05:59.220
which means it starts in
the feet and the hands.

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:02.820
And I've shown you a picture
of a woman, a patient of mine,

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:06.390
who has the erythromelalgia
phenotype, which

00:06:06.390 --> 00:06:10.980
means that in addition to having
painful legs, they're also red,

00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:11.970
and they're swollen.

00:06:11.970 --> 00:06:14.040
So when we see those
three things together,

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:16.230
the Greek for that
is erythromelalgia.

00:06:16.230 --> 00:06:20.570
It's just a particular flavor
of small fiber neuropathy.

00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:22.430
Not everybody with
erythromelalgia

00:06:22.430 --> 00:06:26.130
has this neuropathy,
but at least 50% do.

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:29.130
And for those of you with a
particular interest in this,

00:06:29.130 --> 00:06:33.570
there is May 9th,
