00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:45.590
- After we wrote
papers on shingles,

00:49:45.590 --> 00:49:49.000
and we turned our attention to
complex regional pain syndrome,

00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:51.030
which has a lot of
similar symptoms--

00:49:51.030 --> 00:49:56.790
the unexplained pain, swelling,
color changes, changes in hair,

00:49:56.790 --> 00:50:00.480
and we published the first
objective evidence that that is

00:50:00.480 --> 00:50:04.170
what we call a regional
small fiber neuropathy,

00:50:04.170 --> 00:50:07.860
where only a part of the
body's nerves are affected.

00:50:07.860 --> 00:50:10.450
I've been telling you
about polyneuropathy,

00:50:10.450 --> 00:50:13.200
which means it's a
generalized nerve problem.

00:50:13.200 --> 00:50:16.680
So yes, we think CRPS
is very closely linked,

00:50:16.680 --> 00:50:19.380
and that it's a regional
small fiber neuropathy.

00:50:19.380 --> 00:50:21.960
And furthermore,
CRPS, which is when

00:50:21.960 --> 00:50:25.890
people have a kind of an
injury, a skiing accident,

00:50:25.890 --> 00:50:27.930
or cut their leg, or a sprain.

00:50:27.930 --> 00:50:30.240
It's something that
would just get better,

00:50:30.240 --> 00:50:32.520
and for whatever reason,
it just doesn't get better,

00:50:32.520 --> 00:50:36.374
and the pain, and problems
can go on for years sometimes.

00:50:36.374 --> 00:50:38.040
We think that in some
of those patients,

00:50:38.040 --> 00:50:41.700
they may actually have
an underlying small fiber

00:50:41.700 --> 00:50:44.370
polyneuropathy, and
it's for that reason

00:50:44.370 --> 00:50:47.040
that their nerves
aren't able to recover

00:50:47.040 --> 00:50:49.114
after they've been injured.

