01:06:31.350 --> 01:06:34.080
immunoglobulins taken
from blood donors,

01:06:34.080 --> 01:06:36.840
such as us, healthy
blood donors--

01:06:36.840 --> 01:06:39.390
comparing it when it's
given intravenously,

01:06:39.390 --> 01:06:43.920
which is what IVIg stands for,
as opposed to subcutaneously,

01:06:43.920 --> 01:06:44.910
which is SCIg.

01:06:47.550 --> 01:06:49.830
There are pros and cons
of giving it either way.

01:06:49.830 --> 01:06:51.760
They both get it into your body.

01:06:51.760 --> 01:06:54.270
They're both effective.

01:06:54.270 --> 01:06:56.090
It's really a logistic
issue, and there

01:06:56.090 --> 01:06:59.200
are different logistics,
different insurance companies

01:06:59.200 --> 01:07:01.830
approve it in different ways.

01:07:01.830 --> 01:07:05.370
By the way, I'm telling you
this that we published a paper,

01:07:05.370 --> 01:07:08.880
that it's reasonably effective
as if that means you can then

01:07:08.880 --> 01:07:11.160
go out, and get it.

01:07:11.160 --> 01:07:13.860
Maybe you know already,
but for the rest

01:07:13.860 --> 01:07:17.100
of the audience is that the
insurance companies pretty

01:07:17.100 --> 01:07:20.100
much don't approve
these treatments,

01:07:20.100 --> 01:07:25.060
and it's very rare that
they will approve it.

01:07:25.060 --> 01:07:27.730
The reason is they don't
come to lectures like this.

01:07:27.730 --> 01:07:31.240
There aren't any
medical insurance?

01:07:31.240 --> 01:07:33.160
See?

01:07:33.160 --> 01:07:34.450
I told you so.

01:07:34.450 --> 01:07:35.680
I told you so.

01:07:35.680 --> 01:07:37.660
And because of
that, they may not

01:07:37.660 --> 01:07:40.780
know the things that are
emerging from the leading

01:07:40.780 --> 01:07:42.730
research universities.

01:07:42.730 --> 01:07:45.190
And so therefore,
even though things

01:07:45.190 --> 01:07:48.280
were published, when your
doc tries to get approval

01:07:48.280 --> 01:07:52.840
for treatment, whether it's
subcutaneous or IV, pretty

01:07:52.840 --> 01:07:56.060
much, typically, the
response is no way.

01:07:56.060 --> 01:07:59.440
That's why we put our
paper on the website.

01:07:59.440 --> 01:08:00.940
And if your sister
is interested,

01:08:00.940 --> 01:08:03.280
she needs to get a
copy of that paper

01:08:03.280 --> 01:08:06.820
because you have to physically
take the published evidence,

01:08:06.820 --> 01:08:08.920
give it to your own
treating doctor,

01:08:08.920 --> 01:08:11.440
and have your treating
doctor send it

01:08:11.440 --> 01:08:13.300
to the insurance company.

01:08:13.300 --> 01:08:17.229
And say, well, hey, now there
is evidence that it works.

01:08:17.229 --> 01:08:19.270
So please consider it.

01:08:19.270 --> 01:08:19.810
