01:08:42.640 --> 01:08:44.200
Yes, very important.

01:08:44.200 --> 01:08:45.414
Very interesting.

01:08:52.500 --> 01:08:53.100
- Hi.

01:08:53.100 --> 01:08:54.250
Thank you.

01:08:54.250 --> 01:08:56.779
I have one question
that may just

01:08:56.779 --> 01:08:58.939
be restating what
you've said, so I

01:08:58.939 --> 01:09:01.880
apologize if that is all it is.

01:09:01.880 --> 01:09:04.550
But just to clarify, if
you had a patient whose

01:09:04.550 --> 01:09:08.550
say, had a diagnosis of
POTS, and fibromyalgia,

01:09:08.550 --> 01:09:11.840
just as an example, maybe
they were poorly controlled,

01:09:11.840 --> 01:09:19.970
is that enough to say
let's test for this?

01:09:19.970 --> 01:09:24.109
Or are there specific
physical symptoms

01:09:24.109 --> 01:09:28.020
that they should have as well?

01:09:28.020 --> 01:09:29.870
- That's a great question.

01:09:29.870 --> 01:09:33.380
That is a great question.

01:09:33.380 --> 01:09:37.729
And I think, again,
it's an emerging area.

01:09:37.729 --> 01:09:39.779
It's very unclear.

01:09:39.779 --> 01:09:43.010
We don't know for sure who
will, who will not have this.

01:09:43.010 --> 01:09:45.620
We don't even have-- as with
the skin biopsy question,

01:09:45.620 --> 01:09:47.720
